        "created_at": "2010-11-18T00:03:57.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>i think i havent explained well, i was a little in a hurry</p>\n<p>just becouse they can be rendered and displayed as 3d, it doens mean that they are stored as a 3d file and there are evidences of the use of heightmap as no vertical terrain, the only vertical (and/or inverted) things are objects such as buildings, cave entrances, bridges</p>\n<p>sorry if im a little confusing, not too good at english</p>",
