      {
        "id": 364954,
        "name": null,
        "username": "Battler",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/battler/{size}/208_2.png",
        "created_at": "2011-05-21T15:09:18.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I know for a fact at least the LbaNet Team, as well as another Team out there on this forum, know the full format for LBA 2 islands, models, etc., however all my requests to them to disclose the format so us modders can develop modding tools for those things based on those formats, have gone so far ignored.</p>\n<p>But yes, indeed the islands are made from height maps, with buildings etc. on the being in 3-D. In fact, youll find theres a LBA 2 Island Height Map Viewer made by me floating around somewhere. But its not just height map, its height map along with other data which I am currently not able to decipher.<br>\nEach island is split in two files, one with extension .ILE, which has the height maps and other data required for actually rendering the island itself, and the other has extension .OBL which has the 3-D models for the buildings, etc. <img src=\"//forum.magicball.net/plugins/discourse-lba-emoji/images/takam/wink.png?v=12\" title=\":wink:\" class=\"emoji emoji-custom\" alt=\":wink:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>",
