        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/rincevent_123/{size}/476_2.png",
        "created_at": "2011-09-21T08:22:51.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Never seen this thread before.</p>\n<p>So yes the lba2 island is a mix of height map for the ground and 3D objects for buildings.<br>\nWe are pretty close from having the whole format decoded but there is still a few glitches here and there.</p>\n<p>The c++ code I am using to decode the format is mainly coming from the LbaOnline project from Link.<br>\nThe source code is freely available fro everyone on subversion here: <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/neolbanet/source/checkout\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Google Code Archive - Long-term storage for Google Code Project Hosting.</a></p>\n<p>You will find the tool to convert the lba2 island format under Tools/Lba2MapExporter</p>\n<p>Hope this helps</p>",
        "post_number": 9,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 11,
        "updated_at": "2024-10-25T18:49:16.960Z",
